&lt;p&gt;Welcome to this blog. It pretends to be a "live" record of my experimentations with &lt;a href="https://www.python.org/"&gt;Python&lt;/a&gt; code in general, and its use in economic research in particular. I hope it will allow me:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To discipline myself into writing my ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To share some of my interests with potential readers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To learn to code and to use code better.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let's see how far can we go with this little &lt;a href="https://github.com/getpelican/pelican"&gt;Pelican&lt;/a&gt; thing! To &lt;span class="math"&gt;\(\infty\)&lt;/span&gt; and beyond!&lt;/p&gt;
